qas.question: What insects feed on other insects?
Insectivorous insects are beneficial or harmful to humans?
What are the most visible predators of insects?
What is the largest consumer of insects?

context: <a0_0>Insectivorous<a0_0/> insects, or insects which feed on other insects, are <a1_0>beneficial<a1_0/> to humans because they eat insects that could cause damage to agriculture and human structures. For example, aphids feed on crops and cause problems for farmers, but <a2_0>ladybugs<a2_0/> feed on aphids, and can be used as a means to get significantly reduce pest aphid populations. While <a3_0>birds<a3_0/> are perhaps more visible predators of insects, <a4_0>insects themselves<a4_0/> account for the vast majority of insect consumption. Ants also help control animal populations by consuming small vertebrates. Without predators to keep them in check, insects can undergo almost unstoppable population explosions.:328–348:400
